HEADWORD: Racemation
<hw>Rac`e*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧s`⟦esl⟧*m⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>racematio</ets> a gleaning, fr.
<ets>racemari</ets> to glean, <ets>racemus</ets> a cluster of grapes.
See <er>Raceme</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A cluster or bunch, as of
grapes.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Cultivation or gathering of clusters of
grapes.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Burnet.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Raceme</ent>⟦br⟧
